description: Police were called to Richmond Hill Drive in Bournemouth on Monday evening.
title: Two men seriously injured in Bournemouth stabbing
title_page: Two men seriously injured in Bournemouth stabbing - BBC News
maintext:
Two men have been seriously injured after a stabbing in Bournemouth where a woman was also assaulted.
Dorset Police said they were called to Richmond Hill Drive in Bournemouth at 19:23 GMT on Monday.
A 21-year-old man from Bournemouth and a man in his 30s from Southampton were both taken to hospital, and the 21-year-old was arrested on suspicion of causing grievous bodily harm with intent.
Police said a woman in her 30s was also assaulted but did not sustain any serious injuries.
